SIMPLE: transversal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transversal
<hw>Trans*ver"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>transversal</ets>. See <er>Transverse</er>.]</ety> <def>Running or
lying across; transverse; <as>as, a <ex>transversal</ex>
line</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Trans*ver"sal*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transversal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transversal
<hw>Trans*ver"sal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>transversale</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A straight line
which traverses or intersects any system of other lines, as a line
intersecting the three sides of a triangle or the sides
produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transverse</ent>⟦br⟧
